# C++ Rules

## Language Standard

- **C++20** throughout. Use modules, concepts, ranges, `std::span`, `std::expected`,
  designated initialisers, and `consteval` where appropriate.
- Compile flags: `-std=c++20 -Wall -Wextra -Wpedantic -Werror`.
- No exceptions in hot paths — use `std::expected<T, E>` for fallible operations:
  ```cpp
  [[nodiscard]] std::expected<Order, OrderError>
  parse_fix_message(std::string_view raw) noexcept;
  ```
- Exceptions permitted only in one-time startup / configuration code.

## CMake Patterns

```cmake
# cpp/CMakeLists.txt
cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.28)
project(theeyebeta_cpp CXX)
set(CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD 20)
set(CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD_REQUIRED ON)
set(CMAKE_EXPORT_COMPILE_COMMANDS ON)   # needed by clang-tidy

find_package(Eigen3 REQUIRED)
find_package(nlohmann_json REQUIRED)

add_library(order_book STATIC
    src/order_book/order_book.cpp
)
target_link_libraries(order_book PUBLIC Eigen3::Eigen nlohmann_json::nlohmann_json)
target_include_directories(order_book PUBLIC include/)
```

- One `CMakeLists.txt` per subdirectory that defines a target.
- Always set `CMAKE_EXPORT_COMPILE_COMMANDS ON` (enables clang-tidy integration).
- Use `target_*` commands — never global `include_directories` / `link_libraries`.
- Install rules: `cmake --install build/ --prefix dist/`.

## Conan 2

```python
# cpp/conanfile.py
from conan import ConanFile

class TheEyeBetaCpp(ConanFile):
    settings = "os", "compiler", "build_type", "arch"
    generators = "CMakeDeps", "CMakeToolchain"

    def requirements(self):
        self.requires("eigen/3.4.0")
        self.requires("nlohmann_json/3.11.3")
        self.requires("gtest/1.14.0")
        self.requires("nanobind/2.1.0")
```

- All dependencies declared in `cpp/conanfile.py` — no vcpkg, no FetchContent, no git submodules.
- Run `conan install cpp/ -of build/conan --build=missing` before CMake configure.
- Lock file (`conan.lock`) committed to the repo — update intentionally, not accidentally.

## Eigen

- Include: `#include <Eigen/Dense>` (not individual sub-headers unless compile time matters).
- Prefer `Eigen::MatrixXd`, `Eigen::VectorXd` for dynamic sizes; fixed-size (`Matrix3d`) in hot loops.
- Never return Eigen objects by value from virtual functions (alignment issues).
- Use `.eval()` to break aliasing in compound expressions when in doubt.

## nanobind Bindings

- Binding files named `<module>_nb.cpp` — never mix binding code with implementation.
- One nanobind module per logical C++ library:
  ```cpp
  // order_book_nb.cpp
  #include <nanobind/nanobind.h>
  #include "order_book/order_book.h"

  namespace nb = nanobind;

  NB_MODULE(order_book, m) {
      nb::class_<OrderBook>(m, "OrderBook")
          .def(nb::init<int>())
          .def("add_order", &OrderBook::add_order)
          .def("best_bid", &OrderBook::best_bid);
  }
  ```
- Expose `std::expected` return types as Python exceptions via a helper wrapper.
- Test the nanobind module from Python in `tests/smoke/test_cpp_<module>.py`.

## Formatting & Linting

- `clang-format` with `BasedOnStyle: LLVM`, `ColumnLimit: 100` (config: `cpp/.clang-format`).
- `clang-tidy` checks enabled: `modernize-*`, `performance-*`, `bugprone-*`,
  `cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-*`.
- `make lint-cpp` runs both; must pass before PR merge.
- No `reinterpret_cast` without `// NOLINT(cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-reinterpret-cast):` + reason.

## Header Guards

Prefer `#pragma once` over include guards — it is supported by all targeted compilers.

## Documentation

Every public header opens with:
```cpp
/**
 * @file   order_book.h
 * @brief  Price-level order book with O(log n) insertion and O(1) best-bid/ask.
 */
```
Every public function has `@brief`, `@param[in/out]`, `@return`, and `@throws` (if applicable).
